data.description:
This charming home sits atop 1.79 acres of tranquil canyon land, where the typical Colorado wildlife can be spotted in the large yard that ensures plenty of privacy. 

The home boasts 2 bedrooms, one bath with laundry, a loft for additional living space, and an enclosed front porch to store coats and kick-off shoes. There is also a large walk-through closet in the bedroom while the second non-conforming bedroom boasts niches and even a spiral staircase leading to an office or relaxation loft.  You will find stainless steel appliances, and new flooring throughout. 

The bathroom features nice upgrades such as tile accents and a newly hung barn door which leads to the laundry and a mechanical room with a high-tech water delivery system providing constant water pressure.  The house is freshly painted with 16" composition siding, a brand new grade A roof, a new well pump, and fresh gravel on the driveway. 

If you are looking to be more connected with nature, either permanently or as a second home, this home is just that. Enjoy the best views while biking, parks, hiking trails nearby, or just sitting outside to enjoy the sound of nature... this is the place for you! 

All of this is just minutes from C-470 and US-285, an easy 15 minutes to shopping/dining areas, Red Rocks Amphitheater, 30 minutes to downtown Denver plus South Deer Creek Canyon Road provides an alternate route for US 285 while the bus stop is also conveniently located at end of the driveway. Don’t miss out on this perfect little getaway or homestead!
